HEADWORD: Stethal
<hw>Steth"al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Ste</ets>aric +
<ets>ethal</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>One of the higher
alcohols of the methane series, homologous with ethal, and found in
small quantities as an ethereal salt of stearic acid in
spermaceti.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

